How to setup postbackurl without using 3rd party tracker

To set up a NewsBreak Postback without using a 3rd party tracker, you can follow these steps:

1. Go to Tools > Event Management > Web Events in your NewsBreak Ad Manager.
2. Click on the 'Create/test event' button.
3. Choose 'Postback' as your event tracking type.
4. In the tracking service field, select 'Others' since you're not using a 3rd party service.
5. Choose the event type you want to track and decide if you want to track event value as well.
6. Follow the instructions provided based on your inputs to complete the setup.

For more detailed guidance, you can refer to this article: [How to integrate a general NewsBreak Postback](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25226963388813-How-to-integrate-a-general-NewsBreak-Postback). Let me know if you need further assistance!
Do I need to manually send the data ?

Yes, when setting up a Postback without using a 3rd party tracker, you will need to manually send the data from your hosting server back to NewsBreak. This involves adding the callback parameter to your ad's landing page URL and ensuring that your server is configured to send the necessary event data back to NewsBreak. If you need more detailed instructions, feel free to ask!
in clickmagick how to create postback url ?

To create a postback URL in ClickMagick, follow these steps:

1. Log into your ClickMagick account.
2. Navigate to the 'Tools' section and select 'Postback URLs'.
3. Click on 'Create New Postback URL'.
4. Enter the necessary details such as the event type you want to track.
5. Use the tokens provided by ClickMagick to customize your postback URL.
6. Save your settings and test the postback to ensure it's working correctly.

For more detailed guidance, you can refer to this article: [ClickMagick Postback Integration](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25226963388813-ClickMagick-Postback-Integration). Let me know if you need further assistance!
